node.text:
Entries for this October’s Summer Shredding Classic are coming in and filling up fast. If you want to step on stage in any of the following divisions, click the link in my bio or go to www.summershreddingevents.com to reserve your slot.

1️⃣Men’s Physique
2️⃣Women’s Bikini
3️⃣Men’s Classic Physique
4️⃣Women’s Figure
5️⃣Men’s Bodybuilding
6️⃣Transformation Class (for both men and women)

#summershredding

node.text: There will never be a “perfect time” to start. That moment simply doesn’t exist. It’s simple. Find something you’re passionate about. Set a goal that intimidates you. A goal that seems far fetched and a little crazy at first... Then... Execute. Find a way. If you don’t find one, make one. Don’t stop until you’re there. #summershredding2020

node.text:
Four months ago just the THOUGHT of me committing myself to getting in the best shape of my life and actually COMING BACK to YouTube seemed both mentally and physically unrealistic, crazy, and uncalled for (to the people around me and honestly - to myself).

How could you possibly handle anymore responsibility and stress? Why waste your energy counting calories when you have much “bigger / more URGENT” things to worry about? You’ve been a ghost on social media for over a year… and you’re still growing and making money - why add getting shredded and filming to your plate?

Yesterday marked 100 days into my Summer Shredding prep… and here’s the funny thing.

- I’m feeling 10X stronger
- I’m much more decisive in important situations and really starting to notice personal growth as a CEO
- I’m more confident in myself and in my team
- I have MORE time for my family and loved ones
- I’m enjoying my days more than ever

You see - sometimes we get caught up in the stresses and “problems” of life and can allow ourselves to slowly drift away from the hobbies & passions that ground us. Fitness and sharing my life via YouTube is what gave me a purpose back when I was 18 years old. It’s what makes me - me… FIND YOUR ANCHOR and tackle this life headstrong.

New YouTube video going live tomorrow morning - LET’S GOOO!!! 💪🏽

node.text:
Suit Up. It’s time to join the @alphalete family 

I used to believe that if I wanted to get things done right, I had to do them myself. I guess that’s the mindset any young entrepreneur would have to have. This was true… until it wasn’t. I quickly found myself overstretched trying to juggle so much all at once. At some point you have to trust in the foundation you’ve built, put your ego aside and be willing to take a chance on others. This realization hasn’t been an easy one, but nothing worth having is easy. 

I’m incredibly proud to announce that we’ve officially begun the hiring process to find the strong and determined leaders of tomorrow’s Alphalete. This movement has grown into something that was beyond my wildest dreams and now it’s time, with your help, to take it that much farther.

Link in bio 🐺

node.text:
“Bro - what if I started a candy company”

I’ll never forget the countless back and fourth conversations around my pool table. Running all the “what if’s” and potential scenarios together.

Remember, your circle should want to see you win. Your circle should be pushing you everyday. Your circle should encourage you to grow.

If it’s not, start a fresh circle.
